> git bisect points me to b223bec48213060304c09882ce5b3055b15b7e07 as commit which fixes it

Starting from that commit, we process the full command line first, proceed with a number of initialisations, and only then bind ports for inbound forwarding.

> So that said we still would like a guarantee in podman that pasta exited so I say we still need to add the pid argument and wait for pasta to really exit before continuing with cleanup.

...or equivalent (I still hope we can monitor the namespace instead but I didn't get to it yet). Meanwhile, I tried to quickly evaluate the time margin the [accidental workaround](https://passt.top/passt/commit/?id=b223bec48213060304c09882ce5b3055b15b7e07) by @dgibson gives us.

