without that commit, I'm getting 100 failures out of 100 restarts of a "httpd" container (thanks to the additional delay before exit()).

With that commit, I get an average 11.8 ms delay between exit() and subsequent bind() out of 100 runs, and no failures:

```
$ for i in `seq 1 100`; do podman restart httpd >/dev/null; done
$ s=0; j=0; for i in $(sed -n 's/.* \([0-9\.].*\)$/\1/p' /tmp/pasta_time_*.log); do j=$((j + 1)); [ $j -lt 2 ] && p= && continue; [ -z "${p}" ] && p="${i}" && continue; s="$(echo "${s} + ${i} - ${p}" | bc -l)"; p=; done; echo "scale=10; ${s} / 100" | bc -l
.0117600166
```

which in comparison (`pasta --config-net -- false` runs in ~70 ms on my setup) is a really big margin. And that's not even counting the delayed exit().

Let me go ahead and make a pasta (passt) release from the current HEAD, so that we have meanwhile a workaround that should always avoid the problem, in practice, and we can properly address the theoretical problem even if it takes a bit longer.
